          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2020-06-08T21:50:25Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Drug-price Transparency in Communications (DTC) Act</b></p> <p>This bill provides statutory authority for the Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services rule titled <i>Medicare and Medicaid Programs; Regulation to Require Drug Pricing Transparency</i>, published on May 10, 2019. The rule requires direct-to-consumer television advertisements for covered drugs and biologics under Medicare and Medicaid to include the list price of a 30-day supply or for a typical course of treatment, if the list price is at least $35 per month. The rule takes effect July 9, 2019.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2019-05-13T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
